The paper introduces a new approach to sequential decision-making using a model-based planner that can learn to construct, evaluate, and execute plans. This involves using imagination-based planning, which is a novel concept in the field of AI. The paper also discusses how the agent can learn to plan economically, which is a key aspect of machine learning. Given these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.PL.
